		<ul id="questions">
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">What is a Passport?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">A Passport is an identification document issued by a country’s government that proves citizenship and allows a citizen to travel in and out of countries worldwide. A Passport is required to leave the United States via air transportation. While many countries in the world allow free travel with a basic passport, several countries do require a travel visa, for approval to enter that particular country. Please see our list of countries to determine if the country you plan to visit requires a travel visa. In order to receive a US Passport, you must apply for one with the US Department of State, which traditionally is a 4-8 week process. The Passport &amp; Visa Company offers the most efficient way to get your Passport expedited and in your possession as quickly as possible, in as little time as a week. Our simple process of compiling your documents, ensuring their completion accuracy and filing with the Passport Bureau will not only alleviate the stress of this document application, but will ensure you receive your documents faster than any other method.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">How long is a Passport valid for?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">In general, for United States Passports, applicants age sixteen (16) and older at time of application are issued Passports valid for ten (10) years. Applicants age fifteen (15) and younger at time of application are issued Passports valid for five (5) years. Typically there may be some exceptions that include: A second Passport which may be valid for two (2) years. An emergency Passport which may be valid for one (1) year. Lost Passports may be issued with less validity than usual (typically one (1) or two (2) years).</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">Why is a Passport Necessary?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">A Passport is required for any traveler wishing to travel outside the United States or its territories, or if you wish to travel across any between any other country’s borders. The only exception to this is travel between the United States and North American countries (Canada, Mexico, Caribbean and Bermuda), in such cases a Passport Card may be used instead. A Passport can also be used as a valid form of identification for travel within the United Stated (in lieu of a state drivers license).</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">How long will my Passport be valid for?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">In general, for United States Passports, applicants age sixteen (16) and older at time of application are issued Passports valid for ten (10) years. Applicants age fifteen (15) and younger at time of application are issued Passports valid for five (5) years. Typically there may be some exceptions that include: A second Passport which may be valid for two (2) years. An emergency Passport which may be valid for one (1) year. Lost Passports may be issued with less validity than usual (typically one (1) or two (2) years).</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">Why would my Passport application be rejected?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">The United States Passport Agency holds the ability to deny a passport application for a number of reasons. The most common reason for denial however, is failure to properly provide the required documents. The Passport &amp; Visa Company has an expertise for knowing exactly what the US Passport Agency requires, so we work with you through the application process to ensure your experience is seamless an error free. However, there are some circumstances that The Passport &amp; Visa Company will be unable to assist with processing your travel documents. For example, having outstanding child support, outstanding felonies/criminal warrants (not including civil infractions of parking violations), or a prior felony conviction that prohibits international travel.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">Where can I find out my nearest Passport acceptance facility?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">Visit <a href="http://iafdb.travel.state.gov/">http://iafdb.travel.state.gov/</a> to find the closest acceptance facility</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">Why must I appear in person at the Passport Acceptance Facility?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">If you are a first time Passport applicant, or you have lost your Passport, you must appear in person at a Passport Acceptance Facility so an acceptance agent can verify your identity. If confirmed, the acceptance agent will seal your documents, which you then will be able to send to The Passport &amp; Visa Company for your expedited Passport processing. If you are processing a Passport renewal, you DO NOT have to go to an acceptance agency before sending your documents to The Passport &amp; Visa Company.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">What if my name has changed since my Passport was issued?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">If your Passport was issued less than one (1) year ago, you may apply for a name change using the form DS-5504 on the US Department of State website. For Passports issued over one (1) year from issuance, you will need to apply for a Passport renewal, including all the necessary legal documents such as the original marriage certificate or name change document, in addition to the standard Passport renewal documents.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">Why would a traveler need a second passport?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">Due to the nature of having to apply for visas to enter certain countries, and the often lengthy period of time in which a traveler must forfeit possession of their Passport for visa applications, applying for a second Passport is a simple way to ease the travel planning. For travelers who frequent many countries in a given period, or for travelers who may be abroad and need to fly to another country in which a visa is necessary, having a second Passport, will allow one to remain on the job in a foreign country, while getting your visa processed in the US and then mailed to you. A second Passport may also be necessary if you have entrance stamps to Israel and need to travel to countries that forbid travelers with evidence of travel into Israel.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">Does my old Passport get returned when I apply for a new one?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">Typically the answer is yes. However, the Department of State may deem to not return it. If you documents have been damaged, there is a higher likelihood that they will not be returned.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">If I’ve already submitted my Passport application through another means (ie. Post Office), will The Passport &amp; Visa Company be able to help me expedite them?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">Unfortunately at this point in time, our relationship with the Passport Bureau only permits us to pickup documents that we have submitted.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">What if my child is too young to sign his or her name?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">If you are submitting your child’s application, sign your name and print the child’s name.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">Why do I have to enclose a separate fee for the State Department?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">Anyone who submits documents to the Passport Bureau must pay the Department of State fee. This fee must be paid directly to the Department of State, which is why a check or money order in their name is required. Since The Passport &amp; Visa Company is a separate entity, we process our own service fees through our online checkout.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">Why does the Department of State have a different fee than what is listed on your Website?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">The Department of State’s basic fee for an adult Passport application is $110. However, with the associated expediting fees, the cost for an expedited adult passport is $170.</span>
			</li>
			
			
