			</li>
			<li>
				<span class="the_question">What is a Passport Card?</span>
				<span class="the_answer">A passport card is a credit card sized document for use within North American (Canada, Mexico, Caribbean, Bermuda, etc.) for entry by land or port. It’s primary purpose is to expedite entry for certain workers (I.e.. truckers) who regularly cross land borders (Ex. Canada to US). A Passport card is NOT valid for any international air travel. The Passport &amp; Visa Company does not recommend a Passport Card due to it’s limited functionality for travel; however, we can assist you if you call us.</span>
